File managment: A operating system is responsible for the file managment of your computer. It stores these files into directorys. These can include important files pertaining to the OS itself or the files to run a game.
Device managment: An operating system is responsible for managing the drivers and devices connected to your computer. It needs to know what is connected and what drivers are needed to use a device. It is constantly scanning for updates and new input from devices such as a keyboard.
